stylometry: Data mining is the gathering of large quantities of information and bringing it together in order to solve the problem to see if there are any correlations or relationships with the information and data collected.  If there are relationships the goal of data mining is to organize the information so so a person can see these relationships and it can help them to either maximize the profit or cut costs as low as possible.  Data mining can help a person make decisions or determine where there are patterns that are related to the different types of information based on the different dimensions of the problem.  For example data mining can be used to solve a problem in which there are people who are brought into a doctors office and are required to write down their eating habits and their health levels are recorded down.  THey could use the number of times they eat a day, how many calories they consume a day, their weight, their blood pressure, their cholesterol.  The goal of data mining would be to bring all of this information together and see if there is a relationship with the amount of times a person eats a day, the calories they consume and see if this correlates with either having good or bad cholesterol and blood pressure.
